rComments: Professor Koenig-Woodyard is really cool. I love his comics course so much. It's my favourite course this year. His assignments are fair and he's very understanding. He's a genuine guy and I hope to be in his class in future years.

Fantastic professor. Prof. Koenig-Woodyard cares about his students and the material he's teaching. Based on the quality of his lectures, he clearly spends a tremendous amount of time preparing a variety of interesting material. He speaks fluently and naturally, as if the lecture is more of a conversation rather than a lesson.

Really funny professor, keeps the class engaged throughout and clearly enjoys what he's teaching. Essays are imo hard to score well on though, and really drag your grade down unless you have a specific writing style. It's cool that he lets you submit creative writing instead of a big essay at the end though, overall would recommend.

Loved this class and prof. If you like being on your phone/laptop in lecture you don't belong in any of Chris's classes. He puts in the work and it's worth paying attention in lecture and participating in discussions (if you can).
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Chris is an okay lecturer but he's very dry, as is the course material. The tests are what really kill grades. You have to come up with a whole essay over the course of a week or so and then go in empty handed and spend 50 minutes putting it down on paper from memory. It just doesn't make sense. Why not just let us write more essays and hand it in?

He's a great lecturer; very passionate about Fantasy and Horror. He has said this himself- combining both Fantasy and Horror in one semester is very hard and hence, this class was very difficult for me to keep up with the readings (books, and online readings he assigns). Not only that, but lectures are three hours at night. You must work for it.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader']

rComments: An average, decent professor. He's kind of generic in that most of his lecture material is the quality of stuff found on Wikipedia... he talks about the most stereotypical elements of the texts instead of delving deeper for more obscure meaning like other professors. Also, he marks essays very hard but tests not so much. Funny guy though.

Very good professor who is very engaging. He's personable and approachable.  I think he's an average marker, but is very fair. He's open to hearing your interpretation, and will suggest additional things to consider. I've taken several classes with him, and will continue to do so. Money spent on his courses is tuition well spent. Highly recommend!!
I go out of my way to take classes with this professor. He has interesting taste when it comes to assigning reading material and allows for a more creative and open-minded approach to texts.
Good lectures. Tests and assignments are all the same format the requirements are straight forward, prepare to read a lot. Tough marker if you have a decent TA you're in the clear.
his tests have the same format and are easy to study for. he's super fair.

I'm a science major student, so I took his course for the social science distribution requirements.  He incorporates movies, books and jokes into his lectures. The essays are ok considering this was my first time doing one at the university level.

Hilarious professor, he really loves his job too. His enthusiasm and passion shows in every lecture and he always tries to engage the class through jokes and interesting comments. Definitely a good prof to have for non-english students needing to take english.

Rambles a lot. For every single test and the final assignment, he had his TA mark everything. Her marking is extremely brutal, especially when you aren't told what it is she's looking for. She really wants specific details with interpretations that she wants. Even then, he will never do a remark. Not even sure if he marked the final exam or not.
Entertaining guy with jokes, but doesn't really teach.
Prof. Woodyard's lectures were stimulating and the short stories and theorists were great. The creative assignment option was a fun way to engage with SCIFI. Overall highly recommend this course.
One of the most fun and engaging classes I've taken!

Huge disappointment. Doesn't really teach and what he says doesn't really make sense. For an English class you can pass with surprisingly little need to read the texts (his hand outs contain most of the stuff he talks about). But the lectures are largely useless. Would not recommend!

Loved this course & his enthusiasm for Jane Austen.  He makes class so much fun and is always ready with a joke.  For two out of three lectures this was the only class I had that day. I attended all of the lectures. Nuff said.

I adore this professor! He tries to make jokes in class and jokes when they fall flat. He is willing to offer help to students and even prints out excerpts from the novels that he adresses during class. He sends around an attendance sheet, but you won't fail the class if you miss a few lectures. Ovearall-GREAT PROF. Had him in 4 classes.
Great professor! The best professor i have ever had! Easy to follow along and lectures are very entertaining

I don't understand the fascination with him - he's okay, but not great. Lectures as dryly as the material at hand, making the hour a struggle. I'm not a fan of his teaching style; he uses handouts with large excerpts from the readings and his "lecture" is then entirely based on words he bolded. I had higher expectations with him.
He's a good guy, but I find he doesn't really teach. Shows too many movies and cancels class quite a bit. Overall, he's okay, not the greatest.
AMAZING Prof, i take as many of his classes as i can!

Great Prof. Makes lectures fun and interesting. Makes good points that stick in your head and make you understand novel and the author better. Even the ones that are not a part of the lecture. Encourages participation in class by asking questions from students and giving them confidence about sharing their ideas!
Great Prof! Totally understands where the students are coming from. Willing to help. Interesting lectures, great and funny stories!
he's really chill! he's an approachable prof he doesn't act like your a useless person he's actually there to help

One of the coolest Prof's.. I have had him for a few years at UTM and just enjoyed his teaching. Just a pleasure..  Course structure is good.  Although essay topics are pretty tough, if you attend his lectures you would be able to obtain broad themes which will help in writing.
I've taken some courses with him in the past and he is a truly down to earth professor.  He is always willing to listen and to help you succeed to learn.  He is one of my fav't profs at uoft. !
He is a cool person, But I totally dislike tests/exams and he has placed them in his summer course this year, which makes it Not so fun afterall.   :(

Dr. Chris, so far, has been one of my best profs ever. He's farily young and thus manages to lecture as well as entertain his students quite well. He'll interject his lectures with funny/stupid personal stories and brilliant, corny jokes which always want to make you go to his classes. He manages to keep subject material intresting. Also, he actual
he's okay

Quite often many of his lecture topics help compliment my politics or economics subjects.  I sometimes even find myself tlking on subject matters with others due to the various subject relevance he covers.  Oh btw, his hairstyle & glasses make him look like a real rocket scientist. LoL (I think its pretty neat)
I have him for summer.  He is pretty cool.
great prof !.. essay questions can be a bit hard, but if you attend his lectures to understand concepts/themes you should do fine!...

Course material can be challenging especially his essay questions, which may be a bit hard, HOWEVER, he's a all round great Prof.  He knows his stuff well, and communicates it to the class in various insightful styles.  Overall I enjoy him as a Professor and his teaching styles..

I don't know what quite your problem may have been, however I belive it is you since you didnt achieve a makr you wanted..  His lectures are insightful and if you do attend, you can apply the skills/knowledge he addresses into your essays which will give you that great mark.  Obviously you failed to understand that to the dude below...

If this was last year, I would agree with the positive comments, but this year he went WAY downhill. The lectures were pointless and related in no way to the text itself. A course was a waste of my money and time because I can say I learned NOTHING from this class!

CKW is great. He is funny and smart and really encourages participation. He also uses different media to keep you interested (films, music, art, etc.).  I would definately sign up for another one of his courses.

His class can be boring and lacks sturcture. Themes are not clearly deifined, nor are the periods being discussed. However, he is rather helpful when it comes to assignments and flexible with due dates.

Chris was an amazing prof. His class was fun to attend, and subject matter wasalways interesting. His TA (shannon) was the most amazing part. She always had tons of helpful comments. Chris is hilarious, and I learnt alot from him.
Nice Prof.. but hard...
Greatest Prof. ever!
Awesome prof, best professor I've had so far at UTM!
amazing, chris is hilarious, pushes you to do your best, is incredibly smart and is just an overall great prof, one in a million

Well, Chris is awesome and always willing to help. I love his sense of humour and he makes class fun, when he teaches that is. Once second semster hit and he stopped lecturing it went downhill. Even when there are no presentations we just get into groups and waste time. Please go back to lecturing.
a really helpful prof, seems to actually care about how his students progress as individuals.  very enteraining in lecture, loads of helpful e-mails.  A prof really worth while having!

He is an awesome professor! He uses different media types for contemporary analysis of the works used in class. He is funny and smart and definitely a professor I would love to have again. He makes learning fun!
Excellent Prof... Knows his stuff well and clearly communicates to class..  Encourages students to see him for clearity on subject, which is very helpful compared to other Prof's I know
Amazing Prof! One of my favouries!
great prof.  Really fun

Amazing Prof!!!  I wish there were more like him around.  Integrates different media, pop-culture and tells funny jokes to make the class more interesting and provokes class participation.  He's one of the best (if not the best) Professor I've had-EVER.
